   United States Court of International Trade

   Notice of Court Approval of Amendments to the Rules

                On December 18, 2001 the Court approved certain amendments
   to the Rules of the United States Court of International Trade that
   will become effective on April 1, 2002. The amendments and the Rules
   affected by these changes are as follows: USCIT Rules 3, 4, 5, 7, 8,
   10, 11, 12, 16, 17, 21, 25, 26, 30, 37, 38, 41, 42, 51, 57, 58, 59, 60,
   65, 65.1, 67, 69, 77, 81, 82 , a new Rule 82.1, and Rule 89; USCIT
   Forms 7, 8, 13, new forms 7A and 8A; Specific Instructions to USCIT
   Forms 2, 4, 7, 7A, 8, 8A; a new Administrative Order and forms (Notice
   of Consent to Electronic Service, Notice of EFP, Notice of Endorsement)
   with regard to electronic filing, and the “Judges of the Court” page
   within the USCIT Rules & Forms.

             Language deleted from each rule appears in brackets with
   strike-overs. New language is indicated by bold type and redline.


   Leo M. Gordon,

   Clerk of the Court


   January 18, 2002
